MONOPOLY fans from Glasgow will have the chance to qualify for the UK final.The world championships tour bus visits intu Braehead on June 20.The double-decker bus, fitted with ten Monopoly tables, is visiting 12 towns across the UK to find the nation's best player.The winners from each heat will go through to the regional final, while the UK and Ireland final takes place at The Shard in London on July 19.The winner of the adult UK and Ireland final will then travel to Macau, China where they will compete against champions from across the globe.